<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="446" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1050,1437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1050,1076]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species resembles the 
<typeStatus box="[637,685,1051,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lane)" baseAuthorityName="Lane" box="[931,1152,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Keroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singularis">
<emphasis box="[931,1071,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">S. singularis</emphasis>
(Lane)
</taxonomicName>
in the male adult appearance, but it can be easily distinguished from the latter by the suboval and brown maxillary palpus of the male, and the gonocoxites having raised posteromesal part in the male terminalia. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1157,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Keroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singularis">
<emphasis box="[1015,1157,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">S. singularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the maxillary palpus is globose and black, and the gonocoxites have emarginated posteromesal part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
