<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1706,2020]" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[274,354,1706,1732]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[174,1409,185,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[170,1417,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Setostylus triumphus sp. n., holotype. a. head (frontal view), antennae removed; b. wing; c. antenna; d–e. thorax (d. lateral view; e. dorsal view); f–h. terminalia (f. vertral view, with a close-up of gonostylus in the upper right; g. dorsal view; h. lateral view). Slide No. LWS-5-59." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838630/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
) pale brown, with width 1.2 times of its height. Vertex with numerous dark setae, frons and face bare. Three ocelli in approximately linear arrangement, medial ocellus about 1/3 diameter of lateral one. Compound eyes almost hemispheric, covered with pointed setae. Clypeus pale brown with 12–16 dark brown setae. Mouthparts reduced, maxillary palpus with two segments, segment 2 erecting forward, suboval, with 8–10 setae laterally. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[228,308,1850,1876]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[174,1409,185,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[170,1417,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Setostylus triumphus sp. n., holotype. a. head (frontal view), antennae removed; b. wing; c. antenna; d–e. thorax (d. lateral view; e. dorsal view); f–h. terminalia (f. vertral view, with a close-up of gonostylus in the upper right; g. dorsal view; h. lateral view). Slide No. LWS-5-59." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838630/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
) brown and strongly compressed; scape and pedicel nearly funnel-shaped, bearing several subapical and apical setae; flagellum pectinate and 14-segmented, each flagellomere bearing 6–10 setae on dorsal edge, segments 1–8 with a few microtrichia ventrally, subtriangular apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1706,2020]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[295,409,1958,1984]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[174,1409,185,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[170,1417,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Setostylus triumphus sp. n., holotype. a. head (frontal view), antennae removed; b. wing; c. antenna; d–e. thorax (d. lateral view; e. dorsal view); f–h. terminalia (f. vertral view, with a close-up of gonostylus in the upper right; g. dorsal view; h. lateral view). Slide No. LWS-5-59." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838630/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="447">Figs 4d–e</figureCitation>
) pale brown to brown. Scutum brown, bearing dense setae, with a V-shaped streak. Scutellum brown, with a row of marginal setae. Mediotergite pale brown, bare. Anepisternum dark brown, with several setae on top corner. Laterotergite pale brown and subrectangular, bare. Halter length 
<quantity box="[1087,1174,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
, stem translucent; knob dark brown, bearing sparse setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[277,359,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[174,1409,185,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[170,1417,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Setostylus triumphus sp. n., holotype. a. head (frontal view), antennae removed; b. wing; c. antenna; d–e. thorax (d. lateral view; e. dorsal view); f–h. terminalia (f. vertral view, with a close-up of gonostylus in the upper right; g. dorsal view; h. lateral view). Slide No. LWS-5-59." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838630/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
) brown, without pattern, bearing dense microtrichia on surface. Wing margin with short brown setae. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[240,248,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">1</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[322,348,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">4+5</subScript>
with dark setae arranged along the veins. Vein C stops at nearly middle of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1212,1238,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">4+5</subScript>
to M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1299,1307,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">1</subScript>
. Sc ends at basal 1/3 of C, about half length of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[576,584,313,327]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">1</subScript>
. Vein m-cu and R+M fusion subequal in length; Rs about twice of m-cu in length. CuA curved. CuP free, with end approaching to outer margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[269,335,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1973,1997]" captionTargetId="figure-476@3.[344,1243,1461,1950]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Setostylus triumphus sp. n., holotype, mlae, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6856846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6856846/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) pale brown to dark brown. Fore coxa brown. Mid coxa with basal 2/3 pale brown and bare, distal 1/3 dark brown and setose. Hind coxa dorsally covered with sparse setae. Femur, tibia and tarsus brown, covered with numerous setae. Hind tibia with two combs apically, in linear arrangement.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[325,391,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1973,1997]" captionTargetId="figure-476@3.[344,1243,1461,1950]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Setostylus triumphus sp. n., holotype, mlae, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6856846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6856846/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) pale brown to dark brown, bearing dense dark setae. Tergite 1 brown, tergites 2–4 somewhat transparent, tergites 5–8 dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[338,452,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[174,1409,185,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[170,1417,181,1540]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Setostylus triumphus sp. n., holotype. a. head (frontal view), antennae removed; b. wing; c. antenna; d–e. thorax (d. lateral view; e. dorsal view); f–h. terminalia (f. vertral view, with a close-up of gonostylus in the upper right; g. dorsal view; h. lateral view). Slide No. LWS-5-59." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838630/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Figs 4f–h</figureCitation>
) brown. Tergite 9 subtrapezoidal, with abundant setae. Gonostylus curved, narrowed gradually from base to end; basal 1/2 bearing abundant dark brown setae on surface, 8–10 black spines on inner margin medially, and having a triangular projection distal-laterally; distal 1/2 hyaline, bare, with a dark brown apical bristle; hyaline part about twice length of bristle. Gonocoxites brown, bearing dense setae; posterior margin raised and divided medially, with 8–10 black strong spines posteriorly. Cercus thinly digitate, bearing setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" box="[199,418,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="448" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,763,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of this new species is derived from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Qi &amp; Huang &amp; Wu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1034,1148,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Setostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triumphus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1148,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="448">triumphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(victory), referring to the V-shaped streak on the scutum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
